import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['count'])
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the trend of count over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Count'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Rate')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['rate'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month

    month_counts = data.groupby('month')['count'].sum()
    month_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', legend=True)

    plt.title("What is the distribution of count by month?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Month")
    plt.ylabel("Count")
    plt.xticks(range(12), ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun', 'Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec'], rotation=45)
    plt.legend(["Count"])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='rate', by='year', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of rate by year?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Rate')
    plt.suptitle('')  # Remove automatic title
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Rate by Year', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
